**Content approach:** Competitors (nailzinbloom, glamnaildesigns, Bustle, Byrdie, InStyle, NewBeauty, Country & Town House, thenailtech.org) split between personality intros + flat galleries, and pure gallery dumps with captions. NailzInBloom (Jan 2026) is the strongest competitor — takes an identity-driven editorial angle ("Scorpio nails don't whisper, they speak with intention") but still doesn't address the non-Scorpio audience, the soft/minimalist Scorpio, or skin tone guidance. Most posts assume all Scorpios want maximum drama; the "I'm a Scorpio but I want something wearable" reader is completely ignored.

**Visual patterns:** Competitors publish 18–50 images. Higher save rates go to posts with variety across the dark spectrum (not just all-black). The black-plus-one-element editorial approach (matte black + gloss scorpion, black + red tips) saves better than maximalist sets.

**Recommended image count:** 12–16 — curated across the full Scorpio mood spectrum (deep moody dark, jewel-toned, minimalist, Halloween-adjacent). Variety is the key to Pinterest longevity for this post.

